The paper focuses on developing a framework for automatically estimating and ranking the aesthetic characteristics of images based on users' preferences. This involves the use of deep neural networks and interaction with users to construct a unique and exclusive dataset that describes the preference of diverse individuals. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV) as it deals with image analysis and understanding. The paper also involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it considers personal preference and interaction with users. Multimedia (cs.MM) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with visual content. Information retrieval (cs.IR) is also relevant as the paper involves retrieving visually-similar images. Finally, artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is a possible sub-category as the paper uses deep neural networks for aesthetic ranking.
